entities.name: elizaOS
entities.description: An open-source agentic operating system for AI agents, focused on enabling collaboration and advanced features like swarm technology. It aims to provide a platform for managing and orchestrating AI agents.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control and collaboration, allowing developers to manage code repositories, track changes, and work together on software projects. It is known for its extensive use by open-source projects.

entities.name: Twitter
entities.description: A social media platform for real-time information sharing and communication, allowing users to post and interact with short messages. It is often integrated with other software for content sharing and monitoring.

entities.name: AI16z
entities.description: A cryptocurrency token associated with the elizaOS project. Its price performance and liquidity are points of discussion within the community.

entities.name: Llama4 Scout
entities.description: A project or capability noted for its large token context window (10M+) that can run on a single GPU. Specific details beyond this are not provided.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform that allows users to interact via voice, video, and text in communities called servers. It is widely used by online communities for real-time discussions and support.

entities.name: Anthropic
entities.description: A company focused on AI safety and research, developing large language models. Their models are used within projects like elizaOS for AI agent capabilities.

entities.name: Spartan
entities.description: A project related to elizaOS development, with a 'Spartan v2' version confirmed to be in development. A new Twitter account is being prepared for its launch.

entities.name: Odilitime
entities.description: An interim project manager for the Spartan project, stepping in after Rhota's departure. They confirmed the development progress of Spartan v2.

entities.name: Rhota
entities.description: A former project manager associated with the Spartan project, whose departure led to Odilitime taking over as interim project manager.

entities.name: OpenAI
entities.description: A research and deployment company focused on artificial intelligence, known for developing large language models like GPT. It is used as an alternative for AI model embeddings.

entities.name: WBTC
entities.description: Wrapped Bitcoin, an ERC-20 token on the Ethereum blockchain that represents Bitcoin. Its price movements are tracked alongside other cryptocurrencies.

entities.name: WETH
entities.description: Wrapped Ether, an ERC-20 token on the Ethereum blockchain that represents Ether. Its price movements are often correlated with Ether and the broader crypto market.

entities.name: SOL
entities.description: The native cryptocurrency of the Solana blockchain, a high-performance blockchain platform. Its price performance is monitored as part of the broader crypto market.

entities.name: HoneyBadger
entities.description: A community member or entity associated with elizaOS who provided an estimate for the launch of the elizaOS Launchpad.

entities.name: Telegram
entities.description: A cloud-based instant messaging service that offers rich communication features, including voice and video calls, file sharing, and group chats. It is integrated with elizaOS for user interaction.

entities.name: Zilliqa
entities.description: A blockchain platform designed for high throughput and scalability. A plugin for Zilliqa was pending review in the elizaOS project.

entities.name: Kenk
entities.description: A user within the elizaOS community who provided information about available clients and confirmed starting work on a Twitter feed scraper tool.

entities.name: Abderahman
entities.description: A user who provided specific technical advice on configuring the Twitter agent for elizaOS v2, differentiating between plugin and client variables.

entities.name: jin
entities.description: A team member or active contributor in the elizaOS community, who provided answers regarding Twitter issues, roadmap access, and helped resolve user queries.

entities.name: shadows.13
entities.description: A user or team member who provided a technical solution for disabling generated reply messages from Eliza on custom actions by setting a specific flag.

entities.name: SpartanDev
entities.description: A contributor or team member within the elizaOS community who confirmed the current status of the Twitter client in relation to v2.
